    "claim": "When assets are sent to the orderbook, the contract immediately reduces `pool.totalEth`/`pool.totalToken` and `pool.totalLiquidity`, but it does not track any offsetting receivable for the borrowed inventory. `provideLiquidity` therefore mints new LP shares against a temporarily shrunken denominator, letting new entrants buy into the pool at a discount while earlier LPs still bear the outstanding orderbook exposure.",
    "impact": "A user can wait until the orderbook has pulled most of a pool's inventory, deposit a comparatively small amount, receive an inflated fraction of LP shares, and then capture a pro-rata claim on assets that are later repaid by the orderbook. This dilutes incumbent LPs and can directly transfer recovered principal from earlier LPs to late entrants.",
